B. & O. RAILROAD COMPANY, Appellant, v. Louis RUSSELL, Morris S. Borden, and Samuel T. Gaines, Operating as a Partnership under Name and Style of Borden & Gaines, Appellees. No. 8611. Circuit Court of Appeals, Sixth Circuit. March 4, 1941. Harrington, Huxley & Smith, of Youngstown, Ohio, for appellant. Borden & Gaines, of Cleveland, Ohio, for appellees.

Before HICKS, ALLEN, and HAMILTON, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Pursuant to motion of appellant it is ordered that the appeal herein be and the same is dismissed.
